Version: 0.1.19
Date: 2026-04-13

Changes:
- WeChat response reliability:
  - replace `(no response)` fallback with terminal-aware reply rendering.
  - when `max_turns_exceeded` and no final text exists, return a readable guidance message with turn count.
  - when `model_error` has no final text, return a clear retry hint.
  - raise WeChat loop turn budget default from 30 to 50.
  - add `MERLION_WECHAT_MAX_TURNS` for turn-budget tuning.
- WeChat progress updates:
  - push concise per-turn progress messages to WeChat by default.
  - include tool-batch completion summary (success/failure counts) per turn.
  - add `MERLION_WECHAT_PROGRESS=0` to disable progress push.
- Tests:
  - add unit coverage for WeChat reply rendering and progress-toggle parsing.
- Docs:
  - update README and feature notes for progress push and max-turn tuning.

Related commits:
- fix(wechat): terminal-aware fallback reply + higher default max turns
- feat(wechat): per-turn progress push with env toggle
